review_text: What all community gardens should be like.

Très agréables ces jardins ! C’est l’équivalent de nos jardins ouvriers en France.
Nous les avons découverts en allant à pied au pénitentiaire.
Ils jouent en plus un rôle éducatif, on a vu des enfants avec des accompagnateurs s’y rendre avec le matériel nécessaire pour jardiner.
Un éveil à la nature, bravo !
Serene and beautiful garden in the middle of the city.
Cool area for growing your own plants in the city

They got rid of the bamboo  that was growing  it added  character to the garden  besides  a bunch of  trees that  they  planted. The area  where the  bamboo was  could  of been  use for a lot if things . Like  hiding  that big green  storage  containers.
It's great, you must be a member or know a member to gain access to this urban retreat.
Love it.

Happen to be work it in the neighborhood so I stopped over to check this out this was pretty neat we have these a most all over the city but this one was particularly interesting because there was no nasty signs from the caretakers and it seemed the people there were all friendly and willing to explain what they are going and how they grew and share of their knowledge
Nice place or should I say garden. Things here are neat and organized I absolutely love that.Very helpful people and kind. If your in to gardens,planting etc this is your place
Really calm and nice
Gorgeous. Go when they have the food truck festivals. A nice neighborhood event for families and couples.
It's nice.

They always have a wonderful selection of Christmas trees, and I love that they are all set up so you can see them all the way around. Really helpful staff that will load the tree on your car for you.
We got a plot here this year and have really been enjoying the haul from our garden, as well as the community space. It's a really tranquil space in the middle of the city.
Wonderful place
A very nice downtown garden. Came there early April, so plants did not bloom fully. But, there were a lot cherry blossoms surrounding the garden.

Price for having your own lot is worth the time growing anything. Soil they provide is very rich, everyone respects each other's spaces, and shares tools. No public access which is great to keep people not part of the community out, and the fence is secure enough to keep animals out of anyone's way.
Ideal place to spend a quiet afternoon.
Beautiful
Impressive! I've never seen one so large, so lush, so we'll maintained
